This documents what was new in ivtools-0.3 relative to iv-3.2a, the
InterViews 3.2a release from Stanford that ivtools was originally built
on top of.  ivtools-0.3 ran from January 1994 to August 1994, and
represented approximately the third time the team had librarified idraw
in preparation for constructing vertical applications on top.

No change logs remain from this period.  This file is a reconstruction
based on the ivtools changelog history page and comparison with iv-3.2a.

iv-3.2a contained the following libraries:
    InterViews  -- core widget/event library (IV, IV-2_6, IV-X11, IV-look, OS)
    Dispatch    -- socket/signal dispatching
    Unidraw     -- structured graphics editing framework
    TIFF        -- TIFF image support

iv-3.2a contained the following programs:
    idraw       -- drawing editor built on Unidraw
    iclass      -- C++ class browser
    ibuild      -- GUI builder
    idemo       -- glyph demo
    dclock      -- digital clock
    doc         -- document editor
    edraw       -- early experimental drawing editor
    alert       -- notification utility
    (plus many glyph/layout demo programs)

ivtools-0.3 added the following new libraries on top of iv-3.2a:

    OverlayUnidraw -- extended Unidraw framework adding:
                   - overlay-aware component/view hierarchy:
                     OverlayComp, OverlayView, OverlayViewer
                   - OverlayKit: glyph-based menus and toolbars
                     replacing iv-3.2a's Interactor-based menus
                   - OverlayEditor: extended editor base class
                   - OverlaySelection: extended selection
                   - OverlayCatalog: extended catalog
                   - ScriptView: textual save/restore transcription
                     mechanism producing a script format for all
                     graphic types (later unified with comterp syntax)
                   - OvPostScriptView: PostScript output for overlays
                   - Hide/Desensitize capability for graphics and views
                   - NameView/NameState: named graphic views and
                     observable state (migrated from earlier maptools)

    FrameUnidraw -- multi-frame display framework built on OverlayUnidraw:
                   - FrameComp, FrameView: frame-oriented component hierarchy
                   - FrameEditor, FrameKit: frame-aware editor and kit
                   - frame creation, navigation, and manipulation commands

    GraphUnidraw -- graph-node editing framework built on OverlayUnidraw:
                   - NodeComp, NodeView: graph node components
                   - EdgeComp, EdgeView: directed edge components
                   - GraphEditor, GraphKit: graph-aware editor and kit
                   - graph connectivity and topology
                   - graph-specific commands

    IVGlyph     -- a library of extended glyph examples was created
                   during this period (the "glyphs" demo library).
                   The formal IVGlyph library with EivTextEditor and
                   other reusable glyph classes was organized during
                   ivtools-0.4 (fix-02j).

Note: ComTerp (command interpreter), IVGlyph (formal library), and
the Attribute library (AttributeList, AttributeValue, ParamList) were
NOT present in ivtools-0.3.  ComTerp arrived as a standalone library
late in ivtools-0.4, IVGlyph was organized in early ivtools-0.4, the
Attribute library arrived mid ivtools-0.4, and ComTerp integration
with the drawing editors (ComUnidraw, comdraw) arrived at the end of
ivtools-0.4 / beginning of ivtools-0.5.

ivtools-0.3 added the following new programs:

    ov-idraw    -- extended idraw built on OverlayUnidraw (later renamed
                   drawtool).  Glyph-based menus and toolbars, scriptable
		   save/restore format.

    frame-idraw -- multi-frame drawing editor built on FrameUnidraw
                   (later renamed flipbook).

    graph-idraw -- graph browser/editor built on GraphUnidraw (later
                   renamed graphdraw).

Key Architectural Additions

    ScriptView  -- the textual save/restore mechanism established the
                   foundation for ivtools' serialization format.  When
                   ComTerp was integrated in ivtools-0.5, the script
                   format was unified with comterp command syntax,
                   enabling copy/paste over the wire, remote scripting
                   of graphic state, and human/LLM-readable descriptions
                   of graphic documents.  This format has remained
                   consistent throughout 40 years of ivtools development.

    OverlayKit  -- replaced iv-3.2a's Interactor-based menus with a
                   flexible glyph-based layout framework, enabling
                   derived programs to customize menus and toolbars
                   without subclassing the editor.
